(1151, 144, 'single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_4_short_headline', 'Unique visit to our supported animal welfare NGO, Wildlife SOS'),
(1152, 144, '_single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_4_short_headline', 'field_5de87c2645305'),
(1153, 144, 'single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_4_description', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Today is all about NGOs and offering support to some incredible initiatives.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First, we’ll spend the day with the world-famous animal welfare project at Wildlife SOS where the morning will be spent at the Agra Bear Rescue Facility. These bears were once used in the barbaric ‘dancing bears’ practice which thankfully has now been totally eradicated across India thanks to the incredible work of Wildlife SOS. Not only do they continue to care for the rescued bears, but they also run a women’s empowerment program for the local tribe who used these bears for income.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After a home-cooked vegetarian lunch at the bear center, we will take a short 15-minute drive to the Elephant Conservation and Care Center in Mathura. Here you will learn about the important work Wildlife SOS is doing to help the captive elephants in India. And most importantly, you’ll have the opportunity to meet elephants!</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once we’ve completed our education of Wildlife SOS,  we’ll return to the city and visit Sheroes’ Hangout. Sheroes’ is a restaurant and cafe managed by brave acid attack survivors. Here we will learn about their </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">social activism in aid of women\'s rights over dinner, and a donation will be made to this awesome cause on your behalf.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<b>MEALS INCLUDED:</b> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Breakfast, lunch, dinner</span>'),
