(1301, 142, 'single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_4_short_headline', 'A visit to the incredible floating villages on Tonle Sap lake'),
(1302, 142, '_single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_4_short_headline', 'field_5de87c2645305'),
(1303, 142, 'single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_4_description', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cambodia is still considered as ‘third-world’, meaning that it still relies heavily on support from charities and NGOs who take on much of the community support, education, healthcare and more. These support systems are the heartbeat of an area like Siem Reap. They are all unsung heroes who have dedicated their lives to the support and welfare of others. Today we’ll visit a couple of these and give you first-hand insight into the incredible work that goes on here away from the eyes of most visitors. In the evening we’ll head out to the lake for a sunset tour of the floating villages that have existed here for hundreds of years.</span>'),
