(1384, 142, '_single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_11_headline', 'field_5def2e21d54d1'),
(1385, 142, 'single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_11_short_headline', 'A sobering but essential day as we explore the recent history of Cambodia. Final night group dinner'),
(1386, 142, '_single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_11_short_headline', 'field_5def2e21d54d2'),
(1387, 142, 'single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_11_description', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You can’t mention Phnom Penh without thinking back to the times of the Khmer Rouge and their leader, the Dictator Pol Pot, and the horrors that he and his army bestowed on the people of the country. Today we’ll learn all about this horrific period through visits to the Killing Fields and the Tuol Sleng prisons. It may seem a strange activity to include on a tour such as this, however, it’s imperative to really understand the country and the incredible, unforgettable power of the people.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After what will inevitably be a draining day tonight we’ll enjoy our final night group dinner aboard a lovely boat on the river that dissects this fascinating city.</span>'),
