(2842, 146, 'single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_4_short_headline', 'Vietnamese cookery lesson on board our boat before transfer to Hanoi, then to Sapa'),
(2843, 146, '_single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_4_short_headline', 'field_5de87c2645305'),
(2844, 146, 'single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_4_description', 'The day begins with a cyclo (rickshaw) tour around poetic Hue city on the bank of the Perfume River. We’ll visit the Imperial Citadel where Kings of Vietnam’s last feudal dynasty ruled from 1802 to 1945, including the Flag Tower, Nine Holy Cannons, Ngo Mon Gate, Thai Hoa Palace, Nine Dynastic Urns, Forbidden Purple City, etc. In the afternoon, we’ll join a Dragon Boat cruise upstream on the peaceful Perfume River (Huong River) to Thien Mu Pagoda. Our car will pick you up from there for our next stop at King Tu Duc Tomb. The tomb is set in an elegant garden with a magnificent lake and pavilion complex.\r\nMEALS INCLUDED: Breakfast'),
