(2903, 146, '_single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_9_short_headline', 'field_5de87cd36190c'),
(2904, 146, 'single_tour_custom_fields_itineraries_day_9_description', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After breakfast, we’re heading out to beautiful Ninh Binh Province. Ninh Binh has to be seen to be believed just how beautiful it is. We’ll board a small rowing boat to travel the canals amid local villages and lush green fields. It’s then on to Tam Coc (3 caves) which is also called “Ha Long Bay on land”. We head through the caves and then it’s back to the boat quay.  In the afternoon we’ll take an easy bicycle ride to Bich Dong temple, 2 km from Tam Coc, “Vietnam’s second most beautiful grotto”. We then head up the Ngu Nhac Son (Buddha’s Palm Mountain), to be charmed by the marvelous scenery offered by the mountains, rivers, and pagodas. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><b>MEALS INCLUDED:</b> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Breakfast</span>'),
